This paper focuses on the problem of generating text summaries for pull requests in software development, which is a subfield of software engineering (cs.SE). The proposed approach uses a sequence-to-sequence model with reinforcement learning and a special loss function to optimize for the evaluation metric ROUGE, which involves natural language processing techniques such as text summarization (cs.CL) and language generation (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the challenge of dealing with out-of-vocabulary words in software artifacts, which could be related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybersecurity (cs.CY).
